TY  - JOUR
T1  - Academic-Practitioner Collaboration in Management Research: A Case of Cross-Profession Collaboration
AU  - Amabile, Teresa M.
AU  - Patterson, Chelley
AU  - Mueller, Jennifer
AU  - Wojcik, Tom
AU  - Odomirok, Paul W.
AU  - Marsh, Mel
AU  - Kramer, Steven J.
Y1  - 2001/04/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069464
DO  - 10.5465/3069464
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 418
EP  - 431
VL  - 44
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We present a case of academic-practitioner research collaboration to illuminate three potential determinants of the success of such cross-profession collaborations: collaborative team characteristics, collaboration environment characteristics, and collaboration processes. The case study, drawing on both qualitative and quantitative data, illustrates the possible influences of these determinants on research progress, research team functioning, and benefits to individual team members. We identify directions for further work and implications for effective academic-practitioner collaborations in management research.
AB  - We present a case of academic-practitioner research collaboration to illuminate three potential determinants of the success of such cross-profession collaborations: collaborative team characteristics, collaboration environment characteristics, and collaboration processes. The case study, drawing on both qualitative and quantitative data, illustrates the possible influences of these determinants on research progress, research team functioning, and benefits to individual team members. We identify directions for further work and implications for effective academic-practitioner collaborations in management research.
