TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Relationship of Team Goals, Incentives, and Efficacy to Strategic Risk, Tactical Implementation, and Performance
AU  - Knight, Don
AU  - Durham, Cathy C.
AU  - Locke, Edwin A.
Y1  - 2001/04/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069459
DO  - 10.5465/3069459
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 326
EP  - 338
VL  - 44
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the effects of goal difficulty, monetary incentives, and efficacy on the strategic risk, tactical implementation, and performance of teams performing a computer simulation. Goal difficulty increased strategic risk, in part through team efficacy. Strategic risk partially mediated goal difficulty's effect on performance. Incentives reduced strategic risk for easy-goal teams and improved tactical implementation. Teams with both difficult goals and incentives achieved the highest performance. Team performance was positively affected by goal difficulty, team efficacy, strategic risk, and tactical implementation.
AB  - This study examined the effects of goal difficulty, monetary incentives, and efficacy on the strategic risk, tactical implementation, and performance of teams performing a computer simulation. Goal difficulty increased strategic risk, in part through team efficacy. Strategic risk partially mediated goal difficulty's effect on performance. Incentives reduced strategic risk for easy-goal teams and improved tactical implementation. Teams with both difficult goals and incentives achieved the highest performance. Team performance was positively affected by goal difficulty, team efficacy, strategic risk, and tactical implementation.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/3069459
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/3069459
Y2  - 2026/04/24
