TY  - JOUR
T1  - So Close and Yet So Far: Promotion Versus Exit for CEO Heirs Apparent
AU  - Cannella, Albert A.
AU  - Shen, Wei
Y1  - 2001/04/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069454
DO  - 10.5465/3069454
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 252
EP  - 270
VL  - 44
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - ?Heirs apparent? are frequently a central component of CEO successions but have been largely ignored in the succession literature. Our study examines heir apparent tenures and two contrasting outcomes?promotion to CEO and firm exit. We propose that the distribution of power among an incumbent CEO, outside directors, and an heir apparent influences these outcomes. Results suggest that outside director and CEO power are important influences on heir promotion and exit and that heirs who arise from within a firm are less likely to exit.
AB  - ?Heirs apparent? are frequently a central component of CEO successions but have been largely ignored in the succession literature. Our study examines heir apparent tenures and two contrasting outcomes?promotion to CEO and firm exit. We propose that the distribution of power among an incumbent CEO, outside directors, and an heir apparent influences these outcomes. Results suggest that outside director and CEO power are important influences on heir promotion and exit and that heirs who arise from within a firm are less likely to exit.
