TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Impact of Subordinate Disability on Leader-Member Exchange Relationships
AU  - Colella, Adrienne
AU  - Varma, Arup
Y1  - 2001/04/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069457
DO  - 10.5465/3069457
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 304
EP  - 315
VL  - 44
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - An organizational simulation (n = 85) and a field study (41 supervisors and 220 subordinates) were conducted to investigate the impact of subordinates' disability status on leader-member exchange (LMX) relationships. Both studies investigated how subordinate disability and ingratiation were related to LMX quality. As hypothesized, the interaction of disability and ingratiation affected LMX. Ingratiation had a stronger relationship to supervisors' LMX ratings when a subordinate had a disability. Implications of the results are discussed and suggestions for future research presented.
AB  - An organizational simulation (n = 85) and a field study (41 supervisors and 220 subordinates) were conducted to investigate the impact of subordinates' disability status on leader-member exchange (LMX) relationships. Both studies investigated how subordinate disability and ingratiation were related to LMX quality. As hypothesized, the interaction of disability and ingratiation affected LMX. Ingratiation had a stronger relationship to supervisors' LMX ratings when a subordinate had a disability. Implications of the results are discussed and suggestions for future research presented.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/3069457
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/3069457
Y2  - 2026/04/24
